Recording repetitive actions

Similar to VBA macros, automating most repetitive actions in ExcelScript can be done by using the Record Actions tool. This is currently only available on the web version of Excel. The resulting generated script may look like this:

function main(workbook: ExcelScript.workbook) {

  let sheet = workbook.getWorksheet("Sheet");
  // Clear ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents from range A4:A17 on Sheet
  sheet.getRange("A4:A17").clear(ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents);
  // Clear ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents from range A20:A33 on Sheet
  sheet.getRange("A20:A33").clear(ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents);
  // Clear ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents from range A36:A49 on Sheet
  sheet.getRange("A36:A49").clear(ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents);
  // Clear ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents from range A52:A65 on Sheet
  sheet.getRange("A52:A65").clear(ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents);
  // Clear ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents from range A68:A81 on Sheet
  sheet.getRange("A68:A81").clear(ExcelScript.ClearApplyTo.contents);

  // ...

}


Refactoring and abstracting code




Leveraging useful patterns


Ungroup grouped rows

function main(workbook: ExcelScript.workbook) {

  let targetSheetColors = ["#000000", "#FFFFFF"]

  workbook.getWorksheets()
    .filter(sheet => targetSheetColors.includes( sheet.getTabColor() ))
    .forEach(sheet => {
      sheet.showOutlineLevels(3, 0);
    });

}






